SEVEN people, including former Bukoba Municipal Mayor, Chifu Adonis Kalumuna (39), have been arraigned in court to face various charges, including breach of peace. Together with Kalumuna before Resident Magistrate Joseph Luambano were Islam Hanala (49), Antidius Mutajoa (46), Abdulmalik Audax (36), Jovitus Rwebangira (27), Bukoba Urban Chadema Chairman Victor Sherejei (54), and Sosthenes Mutashoberwa (41). Prosecuting, State Attorney Shomari Haruna assisted by Juma Mahona and Suzan Masule told the court that on October 21, this year at Kaitaba Stadium, the accused committed acts that caused breach peace, destroying several properties including a police patrol car with registration number PT 1835, a Toyota, and another vehicle with registration number T9911 BRG, property of Ivan Joseph. Mr Haruna also alleged that the accused assaulted the Bukoba District Commanding Officer (OCD), Babu Sanare. When the charges were read to them, the accused pleaded not guilty. Magistrate Luambano informed them that bail was free as he adjourned the case until November 17, this year.